text: Warren Keith Urbom (December 17, 1925 â€“ July 28, 2017) was an American judge. He was a United States District Judge of the United States District Court for the District of Nebraska from 1970 until his retirement in 2014. He was nominated to the position by President Richard Nixon. Urbom was born in Atlanta, Nebraska. He studied at Nebraska Wesleyan University and at the University of Michigan. Urbom died in Lincoln, Nebraska on July 28, 2017, at the age of 91. Kevin Cole, "Judge Warren K. Urbom presided over key cases during decades long career: Otey capital punishment appeal, Wounded Knee" Omaha World Herald, July 30, 2017. ==References== ==Other websites== * Warren Keith Urbom (1925-2017) Biography Category:1925 births Category:2017 deaths Category:American judges Category:Lawyers from Nebraska Category:Politicians from Nebraska
